  "title": "Infrastructure Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>·   Degree in any Information Technology degree or related sciences </p><p>·    Windows system administration background is required </p><p>·   5+ years of VMWare experience with good knowledge on HCI (Hyper Converged Infrastructure), SDDC, ESX, VCenter and Hyper-V </p><p>· Familiarity with VMWare automation (VRA,VRO) </p><p>·    Hands-on knowledge in Shell, Perl, Python or PowerShell </p><p>·     Familiarity with automated security patch and vulnerabilities management. </p><p>·    Experience planning and setting up project environments across development, QA and production </p><p>·  Experience in software-defined infrastructure software stack </p><p>·   Experience in VActive Directory, Domain Controller, DNS, DHCP, DFS, Proxy and Firewall servers </p><p>·   VCP certification is a definite plus </p><p>·  AWS Certified perferred </p><p>·   Familiarity with the Government Data Centre (GDC) on boarding process </p><p>·   Familiarity with the prevailing Singapore Government standards and policies on infrastructure design and governance </p><p>· Qualified in ITIL or similar qualification in Service Management is preferred</p>",
